==English==
===Etymology===
Recent (post-1995). The prefix "eu-" (from classic greek 'eu' ="true") and the english "[[dicot]]", as this is a name for those (former) dicots that have the true (typical) features of that group. As "dicot" is the short form of "dicotyledon" the uninitiate sometimes jump to the (erroneous) conclusion that "eudicot" must be short for "eudicotyledon".
===Noun===
#'''eudicot''' any plant belonging to the group labelled "eudicots" or "[[tricolpates]]", sometimes ''[[Rosopsida]]''. This group comprises most of the (former) [[dicotyledon]]s. Eudicots are [[birch]]es, [[rose]]s, [[sunflower]]s, etc, but not [[magnolia]]s, waterlilies, etc.
===Adjective===
#pertaining to the group labelled "eudicots" or "[[tricolpates]]": e.g the "eudicot angiosperms".
